BORNTOSTAYTHIRSTY pressed the pace from outside to the top of the stretch, could not keep up with the winner in the lane and held the place. DANCE ELLA DANCE stalked on the inside into the turn, eased out to the three path around the bend, drifted out in upper stretch and finished evenly in the furlong grounds. SELDOVIA broke a step slow, chased three then four wide on the turn and leveled off in the furlong grounds. GRACEFUL SCARLETT brushed the gate to lose a step at the start, chased two wide into the turn, angled over to the rail around the bend and weakened. ANNIE FOX hit the gate to break slow, chased four wide on the turn, five wide leaving the bend, angled out in upper stretch and had little left for the drive.

CORNELIA FORT settled early then moved into range, inched closer on the inside through the turn, rallied inside the top pair from the fence and just missed. TRAVEL SMART steadied behind a rival briefly early, tracked two wide while out of range into the turn, drew closer around the bend and tipped three wide into the lane, drifted inward in the final furlong while finishing willingly to earn a minor award. WESTWARD BREEZE settled inside off the pace, saved ground through the turn, moved out a bit in the lane and lacked a rally. OLIVIA'S CHOICE (IRE) trailed on the inside into the turn, two wide into the stretch and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CRAZY HOT chased from outside to the turn, swept by the leader from outside at the three-eighths pole, quickly cleared and started to open up late on the bend, drifted in a bit and was corrected once with the left hand crossing the eighth pole and widened under hand urging. FIAMINA chased from inside under coaxing early, lost ground around the turn, remained inside to the stretch and kept on to best the rest. HIGH FLYING GRACIE chased from off the pace in the two path around the turn and was along for the show. CONQUEST CELSIUS cleared early and moved inside, lost command past the three-eighths pole, chased two wide into the stretch and weakened. STAY QUIET bobbled shortly after the start, trailed on the inside into the turn, passed a rival on the turn, passed a weakening rival in the lane and failed to make an impact. THIRSTY FOR LOVE raced in mid-pack three wide and failed to menace. LOVME LIKEAFOOL was off a bit slow to begin, coaxed near the back early, took the turn three wide and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SYMPHONY PERFECT (IRE) broke a step slow then tucked inside at the back, went outside a rival into the far turn, angled out at the top of the stretch, rallied widest and got up at the wire. EVER SMART stalked three deep early, bid two wide into the far turn, dueled and took over late on the bend, put away inner rival midstretch, led through the final sixteenth and got nailed at the wire. ANGEL NADESHIKO stalked in the two path, coaxed along around the far turn, tipped out at the top of the stretch, finished willingly through the lane but lacked the needed final kick. ALOHA KITTEN took control early from inside, showed the way up the backstretch, dueled around the far turn and relinquished the lead past the quarter pole, fought on to midstretch and weakened. FOUNDER'S DAY pulled and was rank early along the inside, ran up behind the leader and had to steady at the seven-sixteenths pole, dropped back and raced inside a rival on the far turn and lacked a rally.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOR TEQUILA cleared early, led along the inside through the turn, roused past the quarter pole, opened up in upper stretch, had the rider fumble his left rein briefly at the eighth pole, asked left-handed with a sixteenth remaining and was ridden out late. BIG HAT WILLIE chased off the rail then moved into the two path, spun three wide into the lane, kept on through the drive, could not threaten the winner in the furlong grounds but was clearly second best. BROADWAY UNIONS was off slow to begin, moved up to stalk from inside, saved ground to the stretch, lacked the needed response but churned on to hold the show. BRAZEN BULL stalked off the rail then outside a rival, chased two wide into the lane and flattened. BUFFETT tracked the pacesetter while widest early, ran four then three wide while dropping back on the turn and came up empty. ZIHUATANEJO chased three wide into the turn, angled in around the bend and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TENTH STREET DON sat off the pace then inched closer nearing the turn, ranged up three deep then took over two wide leaving the bend, quickly clear into the stretch, powered away when asked with the left-hand, kept to task into the final sixteenth and coasted in late. PRAYFOROURCOUNTRY dueled for the lead from outside the chased the leader past the half-mile pole, raced two to three wide around the bend and churned on to best the others. MY AMIGO broke inward, went up to duel from inside then cleared outer rival up the backstretch, headed by the winner at the quarter pole, gave up the lead soon after and flattened to third. KING HEAT dropped back under coaxing, trailed into the turn, saved ground around the bend, moved out in the lane and was along for a minor award. APPLE WARRIOR stalked on the inside into the turn, asked two wide leaving the bend and weakened. ARTABKEEN tracked out of range while widest early, rounded the bend four wide and had little left for the stretch run.

By subscription $100 each if made on or before Thursday, May 11, 2023, closed with 15 or by Supplementary nomination of $2,000 due at time of entry. $750 to enter and an additional $750 to sta rt with $100,000 guaranteed of which $60,000 to the winner, $20,000 to second, $12,000 to third, $6,000 to fourth, and $2,000 to fifth. 124 lbs. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of Two Races other than Maiden, Claiming or Starter al lowed 4 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELM DRIVE was away quickly then ceded the lead to FREEDOM FLYER, remained closer up applying light pressure from outside, took over entering the stretch, cleared inner rival and moved inward in upper and held safely in the final sixteenth. HONEY PANTS broke inward, settled along the inside, moved out around the turn and came three wide into the lane, steered out further in the stretch, finished willingly but could not reach the winner. BIG SUMMER raced two wide near the back into the turn, launched a bid while angling out to enter the lane five wide, lugged inward in upper stretch and faltered in the late stages. VERY SCARY stalked in the two path, angled four wide across the dirt, got floated in by BIG SUMMER and lacked room in upper stretch, could not find room until the final sixteenth but was too late to regain momentum. UNA CHIQUITITA (CHI) broke a bit slow, trailed on the inside around the turn before angling out approaching the dirt crossing, kept on to improve position late but failed to threaten. CANOODLING broke inward, stalked from inside, waited behind the leader leaving the turn, gained an opening at the top of the stretch, lost her path at the eighth pole, angled out and could not rally. FREEDOM FLYER broke well and cleared ELM DRIVE to take control early, was lightly pressure by that rival around the turn, was overtaken in upper stretch and weakened in the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 10 1M Turf CR: 97. Starter Allowance Purse 38000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NINEELEVENTURBO was up close early and got bumped three deep into the first turn, settled off the rail, went two wide into the second bend, angled out and chased four deep into the lane, challenged four deep in midstretch, then drifted in to bother rival at the sixteenth pole, cleared briefly and held late. HALFBARBERBINGIE unhurried in the beginning and moved inside, trailed into the stretch, steered out in the drive, surged in deep stretch but ran out of time. LOTTERY PICK tracked two wide then moved inside, saved ground through the far turn, tipped out into the lane, launched a bid between rivals in midstretch, then got floated in by the winner and bumped SEVEN CHARMS at the sixteenth pole and kept on for the show honors. CREW DRAGON climbed while chasing from inside early, moved to the two path and went up to challenge for command on the first turn, dueled on the backstretch then cleared past the half-mile pole, opened up on the far turn, continued clear to the eighth pole, was challenged in midstretch, drifted out to make contact with SEVEN CHARMS at the sixteenth pole losing command in the process and got edged for third late. ONCOMING off a step slow, trailed on the inside early, went outside a rival on the far turn, angled out in upper stretch, improved position but needed to find more to threaten late. FLINT STROLL unhurried in the beginning and moved inside, raced two wide into the lane, angled back inside in the stretch and improved position. SEVEN CHARMS vied for the lead into the first turn then cleared briefly before taking hold to cede command around the bend, dropped back to chase off the pace, cut the corner into the stretch, angled out and tried to rally between foes before being sandwiched and checking at the sixteenth pole which halted all late momentum. DURANTE showed early speed then became rank and drifted out a bit on the first turn, dropped back to stalk off the pace, chased two wide then between foes on the far turn and weakened in the drive. STOTLAND broke a step slow, chased three then two wide early, ran two then three wide around the second bend, angled out into the stretch and failed to menace. ROSENQUIST forwardly placed four deep then got floated out a bit on the first turn, went up to duel three deep leaving the first turn, chased the leader past the half-mile pole, traveled two wide then three deep into the lane and faded. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY THERE WAS A DOUBLE DISQUALIFICATION REGARDING THE SAME INCIDENT AT THE SIXTEENTH POLE. THE STEWARDS FIRST DISQUALIFIED NINEELEVENTURBO FROM FIRST TO SIXTH FOR DRIFTING IN AND FORCING LOTTERY PICK INTO SEVEN CHARMS. THE STEWARDS THEN DISQUALIFIED CREW DRAGON FROM FOURTH TO SEVENTH FOR DRIFTING OUT AND MAKING CONTACT WITH SEVEN CHARMS.
